A vintage 1960s-style travel poster composition featuring Singapore's iconic Marina Bay skyline with its distinctive skyscrapers and the Merlion silhouette in the foreground. Fighter jets streak across a warm sunset sky in formation, leaving colorful trails behind them. The scene is rendered in bold, saturated retro colors—deep oranges, teals, and golds—with visible halftone dot patterns and slightly faded edges typical of mid-century advertising prints. Palm fronds frame the corners, and the overall mood conveys excitement, prestige, and elite professional training in an exotic Asian destination.
